race.comment: Matt Dunn-trained MRS GOLDBERG (11) led all the way to score on debut over 1000m at Coffs Harbour and has not raced since. Owns a  Murwillumbah trial win and will be naturally improved. A candidate to lead and will take beating. STEFFI ELECTRICA (7) resumes and is also in good hands. Brings strong form and won a recent Beaudesert trial. Thornton stays aboard and the first up form is good.  DAITANNA (3) won her Maiden at the Sunshine Coast as expected and won't have to improve much to feature. She has a sticky gate to manage. BOLD BIDDER (1) has switched to a metro yard and won a recent trial. On a 59-day return and is worth a betting watch.
